Program: Outlook
Title: On a Mission with Haiti's Air Ambulance
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p049wktk
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 12 Oct 2016
Melissa Mecklembourg is a nurse with Haiti's air ambulance service helping in the aftermath of Hurricane Matthew. Amos Bernard from Sri Lanka was a Tamil Tiger rebel but is now part of a theatre group that travels round villages performing dramas about the country's social problems. Bill Yoachim from Canada is an Indian from the First Nations group and is now a campaigner on mental health issues. Samuel Tsang, a financial worker from London, relaxes by folding paper. He has written a book about origami. (Photo: An air ambulance helicopter in flight. Credit: Haiti Air Ambulance) Show less